Paper: hep-th/9907189

Date: 1999-07-26

Title: Anomalies in String Theory with D-Branes

Authors: Daniel S. Freed, Edward Witten

Comments: 39 pages, 2 figures; revised version adds a reference

We analyze global anomalies for elementary Type II strings in the presence ofD-branes. Global anomaly cancellation gives a restriction on the D-branetopology. This restriction makes possible the interpretation of D-brane chargeas an element of K-theory.